273
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:54,070
I was pretty sure I wanted you...

274
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:56,800
...but I just thought we should meet face to face.

275
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,690
I've made my decision.

276
00:11:59,430 --> 00:12:01,240
I choose them.

277
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:03,980
Oh, my God, this is great.

278
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:06,150
This is so great. Did you hear that?

279
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,810
Yeah, I did.

280
00:12:07,860 --> 00:12:08,970
Hey.

281
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:12,730
Thank you. Thank you so much.

282
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,690
You are so going to heaven!

283
00:12:23,050 --> 00:12:25,470
We got some really great stuff.

284
00:12:25,470 --> 00:12:26,680
Yeah.

285
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:29,370
Yeah, but I'm not sure about some of the bras I got.

286
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,780
Really? Do you want to try some of them on for me?

287
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:33,050
Okay.

288
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:36,240
Wait, are we in Joey's imagination?

289
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:42,240
Oh, no. I took one of Ross' bags by mistake.

290
00:12:42,290 --> 00:12:43,870
And one of mine is missing.

291
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:45,300
Ross probably has it.

292
00:12:45,350 --> 00:12:46,890
You'll get it from him later.

293
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:55,230
So, what do you think?

294
00:12:57,820 --> 00:13:00,630
I think we're not wearing the same shirt anymore.

295
00:13:02,060 --> 00:13:04,550
Yeah. Yeah, Rachel picked it out for me.

296
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:06,070
She told me to trust her, and you know what?

297
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,340
I'm glad I did.

298
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:09,790
I turned quite a few heads on my way over here.

299
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:14,930
Dude, I really don't think you should be wearing that.

300
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:17,440
I see.

301
00:13:17,490 --> 00:13:20,990
Somebody's afraid of a little competition with the ladies?

302
00:13:22,110 --> 00:13:24,600
Looks like someone is the ladies!

303
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:28,870
You're just jealous because you couldn't pull this off.

304
00:13:29,130 --> 00:13:32,620
Yeah. Now if you'll excuse me, I have a date.

305
00:13:34,770 --> 00:13:38,170
See? All eyes on me!

306
00:13:44,110 --> 00:13:46,010
We are not signing those papers.

307
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:47,400
Why not?

308
00:13:47,450 --> 00:13:49,940
It's wrong. They made a mistake.

309
00:13:49,990 --> 00:13:51,340
They think we're somebody else.

310
00:13:51,390 --> 00:13:53,760
God works in mysterious ways.

311
00:13:54,550 --> 00:13:56,330
You have got to stop.

312
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:59,010
But she liked us.

313
00:13:59,060 --> 00:14:00,660
She likes Doctor Chandler

314
00:14:00,710 --> 00:14:02,020
and Reverend Monica.

315
00:14:02,510 --> 00:14:03,900
If you think about it,

316
00:14:03,950 --> 00:14:05,680
I'm kind of like a reverend.

317
00:14:05,730 --> 00:14:09,440
I mean, as a chef, I serve God

318
00:14:09,490 --> 00:14:12,390
by feeding the hungry and poor.

319
00:14:13,070 --> 00:14:15,960
Your veal chop is 34.95!

320
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,410
Come on,

321
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:20,530
I just-- I think we've been given an opportunity.

322
00:14:20,580 --> 00:14:22,120
The mistake's already made.

323
00:14:22,170 --> 00:14:23,710
They're writing up the papers now.

324
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:25,670
But we're not the ones she chose.

325
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,080
How can you feel okay about this?

326
00:14:29,620 --> 00:14:31,010
Because.

327
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:34,880
We may not be who she thinks we are...

328
00:14:34,930 --> 00:14:37,710
...but no one will ever love that baby more than us.

329
00:14:37,830 --> 00:14:39,810
- I know.  - I mean, who knows...

330
00:14:39,860 --> 00:14:41,300
...how long it's gonna take for someone else

331
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:42,850
to give us a baby?

332
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:45,550
What if no one ever picks us?

333
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,180
Oh, honey....

334
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:48,860
Please?

335
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:51,530
Please. We are so close.

336
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:55,600
Monica, I want a baby too.

337
00:14:56,130 --> 00:14:58,520
But this woman is giving away her child.

338
00:14:58,570 --> 00:15:01,400
She deserves to know who it's going to.

339
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,590
Okay. You're right.

340
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:15,400
So we'll tell the truth.

341
00:15:15,450 --> 00:15:16,580
And who knows, you know?

342
00:15:16,630 --> 00:15:18,510
Maybe she'll like us for us.

343
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:22,960
Maybe she will.

344
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:26,270
Why couldn't I have been a reverend?

345
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,770
You're Jewish.

346
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:31,550
Technicality!

347
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:39,470
Garden salad for the lady.

348
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:41,900
Oh, that looks great. Good ordering.

349
00:15:42,660 --> 00:15:45,310
Seafood platter for the gentleman,

350
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:46,900
and extra fries.

351
00:15:46,950 --> 00:15:48,150
Enjoy.

352
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,550
Those fries look delicious.

353
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:55,220
I didn't know you liked French fries.

354
00:15:55,270 --> 00:15:57,690
Help yourself. What's mine is yours.

355
00:16:02,570 --> 00:16:04,600
Wow, are those stuffed clams?

356
00:16:09,050 --> 00:16:11,420
Yes, they are my stuffed clams.

357
00:16:13,830 --> 00:16:16,640
How about those fries, though, huh?

358
00:16:17,590 --> 00:16:20,320
- They are delicious.  - Yeah.

359
00:16:23,570 --> 00:16:26,610
You are beautiful, you know that?

360
00:16:28,140 --> 00:16:30,330
That is so sweet.

361
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:33,670
Okay, then.

362
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:47,280
Now look what you did!

363
00:16:47,330 --> 00:16:50,000
What? What is the matter with you?

364
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,230
I don't like it

365
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:54,090
when people take food off of my plate, okay?

366
00:16:54,140 --> 00:16:55,980
But you said, "What's mine is yours."

367
00:16:56,030 --> 00:16:57,600
Well, I didn't mean it!

368
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:01,020
Fine. Sorry,

369
00:17:01,070 --> 00:17:03,350
I didn't think it was that big a deal.

370
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,860
No, I'm sorry. I....

371
00:17:06,910 --> 00:17:09,190
I'm overreacting, okay?

372
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,790
It's just, when it comes to food, l...

373
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:13,190
...have certain rules...

374
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,020
...okay? I mean...

375
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:17,030
...there are things you do,

376
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:19,990
and, you know, things that you don't do.

377
00:17:27,230 --> 00:17:29,180
Wow, this place looks great.

378
00:17:29,230 --> 00:17:30,590
Oh, you are gonna love it.

379
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:33,840
And I'm so glad we're finally doing this.

380
00:17:33,890 --> 00:17:36,330
- Me too.  - Here.

381
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,950
So this was fun.

382
00:17:55,660 --> 00:17:58,500
I really am sorry about, you know, before.

383
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:00,300
And I want to make sure you know

384
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:01,750
I really do like you.

385
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:04,720
Sure, just not as much as clams.

386
00:18:04,770 --> 00:18:06,420
Well, stuffed clams....

387
00:18:08,340 --> 00:18:10,490
Chocolate torte for the lady.

388
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:12,570
Cheesecake for the gentleman.

389
00:18:12,620 --> 00:18:14,080
Excuse me, sir.

390
00:18:14,130 --> 00:18:17,150
There seems to be some sort of red crap on my cheesecake.

391
00:18:18,810 --> 00:18:21,120
Yes, that's a raspberry coulis.

392
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:22,820
I'm so stupid ordering cheesecake,

393
00:18:22,820 --> 00:18:24,440
trying to be healthy.

394
00:18:37,580 --> 00:18:39,490
Oh, no.

395
00:18:39,870 --> 00:18:41,630
This is work. I should call in.

396
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:42,970
Can you excuse me?

397
00:18:43,020 --> 00:18:44,930
Yeah, sure. No problem.

398
00:18:47,380 --> 00:18:48,620
What are you doing?

399
00:18:48,670 --> 00:18:50,850
I thought you don't share food?

400
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:52,330
Sure I do.

401
00:18:52,380 --> 00:18:53,660
Coulis?

402
00:18:54,590 --> 00:18:57,590
No. If I can't have your clams,

403
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:58,870
you can't have my dessert.

404
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,220
This is a two-way street.

405
00:19:02,930 --> 00:19:04,180
Really?

406
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:06,710
Really.

407
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:09,690
Now this all better be here when I come back.

408
00:19:09,740 --> 00:19:13,160
Yeah, of course. I can control myself.

409
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:27,770
Stop staring at me!

410
00:19:38,970 --> 00:19:41,590
Just a tiny little....

411
00:19:55,990 --> 00:19:58,380
I'm not even sorry.

412
00:20:02,530 --> 00:20:04,260
- Hi.  - Hey.

413
00:20:04,850 --> 00:20:08,730
So these are the preliminary forms for an open adoption.

414
00:20:08,850 --> 00:20:10,150
There's a lot to go over,

415
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:12,070
but I'll explain as we go through.

416
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:16,320
- Is that a picture? - Yeah.

417
00:20:16,370 --> 00:20:18,960
It's a sonogram they took of the baby last week.

418
00:20:19,010 --> 00:20:20,830
I thought you might want to see it.

419
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:29,820
Look, doctor.

420
00:20:34,350 --> 00:20:35,760
Look, before we sign anything,

421
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:37,640
we really have to talk.

422
00:20:40,950 --> 00:20:43,060
We're not who you think we are.

423
00:20:43,110 --> 00:20:44,470
I don't understand.

424
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:46,310
The agency must have made a mistake.

425
00:20:46,360 --> 00:20:47,570
My wife is not a reverend,

426
00:20:47,620 --> 00:20:49,210
and I'm not a doctor.

427
00:20:49,330 --> 00:20:51,310
- What? - That's impossible.

428
00:20:51,430 --> 00:20:53,030
I could perform an operation on you

429
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:54,560
and prove it if you'd like.

430
00:20:56,530 --> 00:20:59,250
I have to check your file. Excuse me.

431
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:01,200
So who are you?

432
00:21:01,370 --> 00:21:04,790
Our names really are Monica and Chandler. We're from New York.

433
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:07,060
Yeah, but the important thing to know about us...

434
00:21:07,110 --> 00:21:10,630
...is how much we would care for this little baby.

435
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:12,840
So you lied to me before?

436
00:21:12,890 --> 00:21:16,390
Well, we "bore false witness."

437
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:19,770
See? I could be a reverend.

438
00:21:21,390 --> 00:21:22,870
I can't believe this.

439
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:25,480
But we were hoping that since we told you the truth...

440
00:21:25,530 --> 00:21:27,130
...that you still might consider--

441
00:21:27,180 --> 00:21:28,980
Giving you my baby?

442
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:31,440
You think I'd give you my child after this?

443
00:21:31,490 --> 00:21:32,570
You don't have to decide now.

444
00:21:32,620 --> 00:21:34,140
If you look at our file--

445
00:21:34,190 --> 00:21:36,790
I don't want to look at your file. This is over.

446
00:21:41,610 --> 00:21:43,110
Erica, wait.

447
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,480
I have nothing to say to you.

448
00:21:45,530 --> 00:21:47,860
Look, you have every reason to be upset.

449
00:21:47,910 --> 00:21:49,500
We did lie.

450
00:21:49,550 --> 00:21:51,240
But only because we've been waiting

451
00:21:51,290 --> 00:21:53,940
and trying to have a baby for so long.

452
00:21:53,990 --> 00:21:55,690
And we don't know how long it's gonna be

453
00:21:55,740 --> 00:21:57,370
before we get another chance again.

454
00:21:57,490 --> 00:21:59,670
Why don't you ask the reverend to pray on it?

455
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:02,650
Erica, please.

456
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:04,790
Just consider us.

457
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,760
Ask them to see our file.

458
00:22:07,550 --> 00:22:09,220
Our last name's Bing.

459
00:22:09,340 --> 00:22:11,980
My wife's a chef, and I'm in advertising.

460
00:22:13,220 --> 00:22:14,570
Oh, yeah.

461
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,200
I actually liked you guys.

462
00:22:19,020 --> 00:22:20,040
But it doesn't matter.

463
00:22:20,090 --> 00:22:21,330
Because what you did was wrong.

464
00:22:21,450 --> 00:22:23,490
But you did like us.

465
00:22:24,230 --> 00:22:25,870
And you should.

466
00:22:26,620 --> 00:22:28,850
My wife's an incredible woman.

467
00:22:29,290 --> 00:22:32,890
She is loving, and devoted and caring.

468
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:35,280
And don't tell her I said this,

469
00:22:35,330 --> 00:22:36,970
but the woman's always right.

470
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:44,300
I love my wife more than anything in this world.

471
00:22:45,910 --> 00:22:47,360
And it...

472
00:22:48,860 --> 00:22:51,760
It kills me that I can't give her a baby.

473
00:22:57,660 --> 00:22:59,530
I really want a kid.

474
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:02,350
And when that day finally comes,

475
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,410
I'll learn how to be a good dad.

476
00:23:05,370 --> 00:23:06,710
But my wife...

477
00:23:07,460 --> 00:23:09,410
...she's already there.

478
00:23:10,150 --> 00:23:11,660
She's a mother...

479
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:14,820
...without a baby.

480
00:23:22,420 --> 00:23:23,950
Please?

481
00:23:36,050 --> 00:23:37,780
You still want that baby?

482
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:56,170
God bless you, Chandler Bing!

483
00:24:09,610 --> 00:24:12,860
Turns out this sweater is made for a woman.

484
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:16,690
So why are you still wearing it?

485
00:24:16,690 --> 00:24:18,320
Because it's soft.

486
00:24:20,140 --> 00:24:22,170
Hey, so how was your date?

487
00:24:22,170 --> 00:24:23,440
Not so good.

488
00:24:26,020 --> 00:24:29,100
Well, looks like it's just the two of us tonight,

489
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:30,160
huh, buddy?

490
00:24:30,670 --> 00:24:32,230
Yeah. And you know what?

491
00:24:32,230 --> 00:24:33,640
We could do a lot worse.

492
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:35,270
- Yeah. - Yeah.

493
00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:41,480
Joey doesn't share food!

